The paper discusses methods for compressing and accelerating Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) without requiring the use of real data, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Given that the paper focuses on DNNs and their compression, it is most likely to belong to cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.CR, and cs.NE.
